How Should One Live Everlasting Life?

Harbut RF.

New and emerging life-extension technologies require careful consideration of 
ethical implications related to resource scarcity and justice, prompting an 
analysis of what, if anything, is intrinsic to experiences we define as human. 
Furthermore, extended lifespans suggest the importance of reinterpreting 
traditional roles of health care professionals as the needs of patients, 
communities, and clinicians shift.

